trans-unit.source: QUdpSocket also supports UDP multicast. Use joinMulticastGroup() and leaveMulticastGroup() to control group membership, and QAbstractSocket::MulticastTtlOption and QAbstractSocket::MulticastLoopbackOption to set the TTL and loopback socket options. Use setMulticastInterface() to control the outgoing interface for multicast datagrams, and multicastInterface() to query it.
trans-unit.target: QUdpSocket还支持UDP多播。使用joinMulticastGroup（）和LeaveMulticastGroup（）来控制组成员身份，并使用QAbstractSocket :: MulticastTtlOption和QAbstractSocket :: MulticastLoopbackOption来设置TTL和回送套接字选项。使用setMulticastInterface（）控制多播数据报的传出接口，并使用multicastInterface（）进行查询。

trans-unit.source: QUndoGroup is a group of QUndoStack objects, one of which may be active. It has an undo() and redo() slot, which calls QUndoStack::undo() and QUndoStack::redo() for the active stack. It also has the functions createUndoAction() and createRedoAction(). The actions returned by these functions behave in the same way as those returned by QUndoStack::createUndoAction() and QUndoStack::createRedoAction() of the active stack.
trans-unit.target: QUndoGroup是一组QUndoStack对象，其中一个可能是活动的。它具有一个undo（）和redo（）插槽，可为活动堆栈调用QUndoStack :: undo（）和QUndoStack :: redo（）。它还具有函数createUndoAction（）和createRedoAction（）。这些函数返回的动作的行为与活动堆栈的QUndoStack :: createUndoAction（）和QUndoStack :: createRedoAction（）返回的行为相同。

trans-unit.source: QUndoStack is able to delete commands from the stack if the command is no longer needed. One example may be to delete a command when two commands are merged together in such a way that the merged command has no function. This can be seen with move commands where the user moves their mouse to one part of the screen and then moves it to the original position. The merged command results in a mouse movement of 0. This command can be deleted since it serves no purpose. Another example is with networking commands that fail due to connection issues. In this case, the command is to be removed from the stack because the redo() and undo() functions have no function since there was connection issues.
trans-unit.target: 如果不再需要命令，则QUndoStack可以从堆栈中删除命令。一个示例可以是当两个命令以合并的命令不起作用的方式合并在一起时删除命令。这可以通过移动命令看到，其中用户将鼠标移至屏幕的一部分，然后将其移至原始位置。合并的命令导致鼠标移动0。此命令无用，因此可以删除。另一个示例是网络命令由于连接问题而失败。在这种情况下，由于存在连接问题，因此redo（）和undo（）函数不起作用，因此将从堆栈中删除该命令。

trans-unit.source: QUndoStack provides convenient undo and redo QAction objects, which can be inserted into a menu or a toolbar. When commands are undone or redone, QUndoStack updates the text properties of these actions to reflect what change they will trigger. The actions are also disabled when no command is available for undo or redo. These actions are returned by QUndoStack::createUndoAction() and QUndoStack::createRedoAction().
trans-unit.target: QUndoStack提供了方便的撤消和重做QAction对象，可以将其插入菜单或工具栏。撤消或重做命令时，QUndoStack将更新这些操作的文本属性以反映它们将触发的更改。当没有命令可用于撤消或重做时，这些操作也将被禁用。这些动作由QUndoStack :: createUndoAction（）和QUndoStack :: createRedoAction（）返回。

trans-unit.source: QUndoStack supports the concept of a clean state. When the document is saved to disk, the stack can be marked as clean using setClean(). Whenever the stack returns to this state through undoing and redoing commands, it emits the signal cleanChanged(). This signal is also emitted when the stack leaves the clean state. This signal is usually used to enable and disable the save actions in the application, and to update the document's title to reflect that it contains unsaved changes.
trans-unit.target: QUndoStack支持干净状态的概念。将文档保存到磁盘后，可以使用setClean（）将堆栈标记为干净。每当堆栈通过撤消和重做命令返回到此状态时，它都会发出信号cleanChanged（）。当堆栈离开清洁状态时，也会发出此信号。该信号通常用于启用和禁用应用程序中的保存操作，以及更新文档标题以反映它包含未保存的更改。

trans-unit.source: QUndoView is a QListView which displays the list of commands pushed on an undo stack. The most recently executed command is always selected. Selecting a different command results in a call to QUndoStack::setIndex(), rolling the state of the document backwards or forward to the new command.
trans-unit.target: QUndoView是一个QListView，它显示在撤消堆栈上推送的命令列表。总是选择最近执行的命令。选择其他命令将导致调用QUndoStack :: setIndex（），将文档的状态向后或向前滚动到新命令。

trans-unit.source: QUrl conforms to the URI specification from RFC 3986 (Uniform Resource Identifier: Generic Syntax), and includes scheme extensions from RFC 1738 (Uniform Resource Locators). Case folding rules in QUrl conform to RFC 3491 (Nameprep: A Stringprep Profile for Internationalized Domain Names (IDN)). It is also compatible with the file URI specification from freedesktop.org, provided that the locale encodes file names using UTF-8 (required by IDN).
trans-unit.target: QUrl符合RFC 3986（统一资源标识符：通用语法）中的URI规范，并包括RFC 1738（统一资源定位器）中的方案扩展。QUrl中的大小写折叠规则符合RFC 3491（名称准备：国际化域名（IDN）的Stringprep配置文件）。如果语言环境使用UTF-8（IDN要求）对文件名进行编码，则它也与freedesktop.org中的文件URI规范兼容。

trans-unit.source: QUrl is capable of detecting many errors in URLs while parsing it or when components of the URL are set with individual setter methods (like setScheme(), setHost() or setPath()). If the parsing or setter function is successful, any previously recorded error conditions will be discarded.
trans-unit.target: 在解析URL或使用单独的setter方法（例如setScheme（），setHost（）或setPath（））设置URL的组件时，QUEr能够检测URL中的许多错误。如果解析或设置器功能成功，则任何先前记录的错误条件都将被丢弃。

trans-unit.source: QUrl is capable of recording only one error condition. If more than one error is found, it is undefined which error is reported.
trans-unit.target: QUrl只能记录一个错误条件。如果发现一个以上的错误,则未定义报告哪个错误。

trans-unit.target: QUtf8StringView接受各种字符类型的字符串。

trans-unit.source: QUtf8StringView can also be used as the return value of a function. If you call a function returning QUtf8StringView, take extra care to not keep the QUtf8StringView around longer than the function promises to keep the referenced string data alive. If in doubt, obtain a strong reference to the data by calling toString() to convert the QUtf8StringView into a QString.
trans-unit.target: QUtf8StringView也可以用作函数的返回值。如果调用返回QUtf8StringView的函数，请格外小心，不要使QUtf8StringView的保留时间长于该函数保证保持引用的字符串数据有效的时间。如有疑问，请通过调用toString（）将QUtf8StringView转换为QString来获得对数据的强引用。

trans-unit.source: QUtf8StringView is designed as an interface type; its main use-case is as a function parameter type. When QUtf8StringViews are used as automatic variables or data members, care must be taken to ensure that the referenced string data (for example, owned by a std::u8string) outlives the QUtf8StringView on all code paths, lest the string view ends up referencing deleted data.
trans-unit.target: QUtf8StringView被设计为一种接口类型;它的主要使用情况是作为函数参数类型。当QUtf8StringViews被用作自动变量或数据成员时,必须注意确保被引用的字符串数据(例如,由std::u8string拥有)在所有的代码路径上都超过了QUtf8StringView,以免字符串视图最终引用了被删除的数据。

trans-unit.source: QVarLengthArray is an attempt to work around this gap in the C++ language. It allocates a certain number of elements on the stack, and if you resize the array to a larger size, it automatically uses the heap instead. Stack allocation has the advantage that it is much faster than heap allocation.
trans-unit.target: QVarLengthArray是试图绕过C++语言中的这一缺陷。它在堆栈上分配一定数量的元素,如果你把数组的大小调整到更大,它就会自动使用堆来代替。栈分配的优点是它比堆分配快得多。

trans-unit.source: QVarLengthArray's API is much more low-level and it lacks some of QList's functionality.
trans-unit.target: QVarLengthArray的API更底层，并且缺少QList的某些功能。

When preparing transmission using CBOR, it is suggested to encode carefully each value to prevent loss of representation.

trans-unit.source: QVector provides these basic functions to add, move, and remove items: insert(), replace(), remove(), prepend(), append(). With the exception of append() and replace(), these functions can be slow (linear time) for large vectors, because they require moving many items in the vector by one position in memory. If you want a container class that provides fast insertion/removal in the middle, use QList or QLinkedList instead.
trans-unit.target: QVector提供了以下基本功能来添加，移动和删除项目：insert（），replace（），remove（），prepend（），append（）。除了append（）和replace（）以外，对于大型向量，这些函数可能会很慢（线性时间），因为它们需要将向量中的许多项移动到内存中的一个位置。如果要在中间提供快速插入/移除的容器类，请改用QList或QLinkedList。

trans-unit.source: QVector should be your default first choice. QVector<T> will usually give better performance than QList<T>, because QVector<T> always stores its items sequentially in memory, where QList<T> will allocate its items on the heap unless sizeof(T) <= sizeof(void*) and T has been declared to be either a Q_MOVABLE_TYPE or a Q_PRIMITIVE_TYPE using Q_DECLARE_TYPEINFO. See the Pros and Cons of Using QList for an explanation.
trans-unit.target: QVector应该是您的默认首选。QVector <T>通常会提供比QList <T>更好的性能，因为QVector <T>始终将其项顺序存储在内存中，其中QList <T>会将其项分配在堆上，除非 sizeof(T) <= sizeof(void*) 并且已使用Q_DECLARE_TYPEINFO将T声明为 Q_MOVABLE_TYPE 或 Q_PRIMITIVE_TYPE 。有关说明，请参见使用QList的优缺点。

trans-unit.source: QVector<T> is one of Qt's generic container classes. It stores its items in adjacent memory locations and provides fast index-based access.
trans-unit.target: QVector <T>是Qt的通用容器类之一。它将项目存储在相邻的内存位置，并提供基于索引的快速访问。

trans-unit.source: QVector's value type must be an assignable data type. This covers most data types that are commonly used, but the compiler won't let you, for example, store a QWidget as a value; instead, store a QWidget *. A few functions have additional requirements; for example, indexOf() and lastIndexOf() expect the value type to support operator==(). These requirements are documented on a per-function basis.
trans-unit.target: QVector的值类型必须是可分配的数据类型。这涵盖了大多数常用的数据类型，但是编译器不允许您例如将QWidget存储为值。而是存储一个QWidget *。一些功能有其他要求；例如，indexOf（）和lastIndexOf（）期望值类型支持 operator==() 。这些要求是按功能记录的。
